-- Greek Bonds Rise for Ninth Day; Longest Run Since Restructuring
-- B y   N e a l   A r m s t r o n g
-- 2012-11-21T09:31:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-21/greek-bonds-rise-for-ninth-day-longest-run-since-restructuring.html
Greece’s government bonds maturing
in February 2023 advanced for a ninth day, the longest run of
gains since the nation’s debt was restructured in March.  The  yield  dropped 20 basis points to 16.90 percent at 9:30
a.m. London time, leaving the price at 33.34 percent of face
value.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Neal Armstrong in London at 
